column2: the following variables are filled (this is a subset of the variables available in the initial .root file

column1: # B_FlightDistance: The distance in mm travelled by the B meson before decaying.
# B_VertexChi2: The chisq of the vertex fit for the 3 tracks
# H1_PX: The x-component of the measured momentum of the first particle in MeV
# H1_PY: The y-component of the measured momentum of the first particle in MeV
# H1_PZ: The z-component of the measured momentum of the first particle in MeV
# H1_ProbK: Likelihood that the first particle is a K (range: 0-1)
# H1_ProbPi: Likelihood that the first particle is a pion (range: 0-1)
# H1_Charge: The charge of the first particle
# H1_IPChi2: The impact parameter chisq of the first particle
# H2_PX: The x-component of the measured momentum of the second particle in MeV
# H2_PY: The y-component of the measured momentum of the second particle in MeV
# H2_PZ: The z-component of the measured momentum of the second particle in MeV
# H2_ProbK: Likelihood that the second particle is a K (range: 0-1)
# H2_ProbPi: Likelihood that the scond particle is a pion (range: 0-1)
# H2_Charge: The charge of the second particle
# H2_IPChi2: The impact parameter chisq of the second particle
# H3_PX: The x-component of the measured momentum of the third particle in MeV
# H3_PY: The y-component of the measured momentum of the third particle in MeV
# H3_PZ: The z-component of the measured momentum of the third particle in MeV
# H3_ProbK: Likelihood that the third particle is a K (range: 0-1)
# H3_ProbPi: Likelihood that the third particle is a pion (range: 0-1)
# H3_Charge: The charge of the third particle
# H3_IPChi2:The impact parameter chisq of the third particle
